rComments: I don't know what these people are talking about. He takes a while to get used to but his exams are right out of the book. He really explains calculus easily once you get used to his accent. I've had calc profs who were TERRIBLE -even ones from Poland- this guy is fine and really knows his stuff.
it's hard to understand what he's saying, and when you do, you realise it's useless. you will end up teaching yourself everything. nice guy, horrible prof... SWITCH.

Absolutely useless!  If you get this prof. run and switch ASAP.  Explanations are weak, assignments are ambiguous and you will not be prepared for them.  Midterms were reasonable, but the final was ridiculous.  You will carry an A throughout the course, then he nails you big time on the final.  Beware!!!!!! My 92% avg. in 4u calculus didn't help.
